{% set alternate_domains = [
    '<https://www.facebook.com/square2marketing/?fref=ts>',
    '<https://twitter.com/Square2>',
    '<https://www.linkedin.com/company/square-2-marketing?trk=extra_biz_viewers_viewed>',
    '<https://www.instagram.com/square2marketing/?hl=en>',
    '<https://www.youtube.com/user/Square2Marketing>',
    '<https://www.pinterest.com/square2/>'
    ]
%}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
   "@context":"<http://schema.org>",
   "@type":"LocalBusiness",
   "name":"{{ site_settings.company_name }}",
   "description": "{{ description }}",
   "url":"{{ company_domain }}",
   "logo":"{{ site_settings.logo_src }}",
   "image": "{{ site_settings.logo_src }}",
   "foundingDate":"{{ foundingDate }}",
   "founders":[
      {
         "@type":"Person",
         "name":"{{ foundername }}",
         "jobTitle":"{{ foudnerjobTitle }}",
         "image":"{{ founderimage }}",
         "url":"{{ founderurl }}"
      }
   ],
   "address":{
     "@type":"PostalAddress",
     "streetAddress":"{{ site_settings.company_street_address_1 }}{% if site_settings.company_street_address_2 %} {{ site_settings.company_street_address_2 }}{% endif %}",
     "addressLocality":"{{ site_settings.company_city }}",
     "addressRegion":"{{ site_settings.company_state }}",
     "postalCode":"{{ site_settings.company_zip }}",
     "addressCountry":"{{ site_settings.company_country }}"
    },
    "email": "{{ email }}",
    "telephone":"{{ site_settings.company_phone }}",
    "faxNumber": "{{ fax_number }}",
    "geo": {
       "@type": "GeoCoordinates",
       "latitude": "{{ latitude }}",
       "longitude": "{{ longitude }}"
    },
   "hasMap":"{{ headquarters_map }}",
   "openingHours": "{{ set_hours }}",
   "sameAs": {{ alternate_domains }}
}
</script>

is anyone having issues with design manager?
I am trying to open a file that i cloned and renamed. When I open it, instead of the new name in the top tab, it flips to the original which i believe is causing issues with my css file now
also, ive been making css changes to file and nothing is happening
sorry guys, apparently when I put the info inside with quotes, it was double quoting at the end. I removed that and it worked fine
<@U2H3TT8F2> I log out and log in when it happens like that
its weird so we're using a theme from the market, they have the company name as the .css file so i cloned it, renamed it but when i open up the clone, its the original file name.
It's really weird now, because i repeated the process and now its not doing it

So what happened which i think is causing the issue is I cloned the original theme file `example.css` and named the clone `example_backup.css`. I then renamed the original `example.css` file to `somethingElse.css`  and moved it into another folder.
I think by doing this, it messed up HS links/redirects causing the issue

so protip:
Dont rename a theme's css file if you use a theme from the marketplace or you will have a bad time
if anyone from HS wants to look into this, I can share the portal with them where this is happening
